@node program "Usage"

    @{"BlueInstall" link Oprogramu} archive consists of two programs:

    @{" BlueInstallPrefs  " link prefs} for creating the prefs file
    @{" BlueInstall       " link BI} main program, is located in @{FG SHINE}bin/@{FG text} directory

    You don't need BlueInstallPrefs so much because the prefs file is
a standart ascii file. You can also edit it by Your favourite text editor.
    @{" Prefs file        " link pf}

@endnode

@node pf "Specify of BlueInstall prefs file"

    Specify of @{"BlueInstall" link Oprogramu} prefs file:


    @{I}Type: @{UI}          Normal Ascii file

    @{I}Identification: @{UI}None

    @{I}Description: @{UI}

First @{I}n @{UI}lines could be used for remarks.
The specific data begin with the keyword @{B}<*Start>@{UB} and should end with @{B}<*End>@{UB}

Between @{B}<*Start>@{UB} and @{B}<*End>@{UB} can be any number of this structures:

# @{I}<Annotation> @{UI}
    The mark '#' mean the begin of @{B}Button @{UB}structure
    @{I}<Annotation> @{UI}is for Your use.

next line is the text, which will be used as @{B}button@{UB} name in @{"BlueInstall" link Oprogramu}
next line is the information text. In @{"BlueInstall" link Oprogramu} will be displayed when
    the user click to the questionmark
next line is the command line. This can define the action with the file
    (eg. can execute install script, show picture aso.)
    It is a simple formating text with following features:
        %d{title}   - this will call the directoryrequester and user can
                      choose the directory (usualy for instalation)
                      Check @{"Example" link example}.
next line is empty
@endnode

@node example "Descripted Example"

    Example:
-- 8< -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
Generated by Blue Install, ©Blue Legend ©1998


*Start

#
Blue Install
Full version of BlueInstall|with the gui
C:LhA -a x Disk1:BlueLegend/BlueInstall.lha %d{Where with Blue Install ???}


#
Blue Legend Logo
Logo BlueLegend in GIF format
Sys:Utilities/Multiview Disk1:Html/BLLOGO.GIF Screen


#
BlaBla
SomeInfo|This info will be on the second line|third
Echo "Some message"

*End
-- 8< -----------------------------------------------------------------------------

    Description:

#
Blue Install                              - the @{B}button@{UB} name
Full version of BlueInstall|with the gui  - the info, the mark '|' mean the new
                                            line
C:LhA -a x Disk1:Bl...                    - this command will be executed

@endnode

@node bi "BlueInstall usage"

    @{"BlueInstall" link Oprogramu} can be found in the directory @{FG SHINE}bin/@{FG text}. This a simple CLI command
with oly one parameter.

    @{B}Usage:@{UB}

        BlueInstall @{I}<PrefsFile> @{UI}

    @{B}The best:@{UB} ... Try it (generate some @{I}PrefsFile @{UI}using BlueInstallPrefs) :-)

@endnode

@node prefs "Blue Install Prefs"

    BlueInstalPrefs can be used for generating PrefsFile (check @{"Description" link pf}).

    @{B}Menu:@{UB}

      @{B}Project@{UB}

        @{B}New@{UB}          - New project

        @{B}Open@{UB}         - Load project from disk

        @{B}Save@{UB}
                    - Save to disk
        @{B}Save as@{UB}

        @{B}About@{UB}        - About this program

        @{B}Quit@{UB}         - bye, bye

      @{B}Generate@{UB}       - @{I}Generating Prefs File @{UI}

        @{B}Prefs file@{UB}   - will generate single prefsfile from current project

        @{B}AutoRun disk@{UB} - will generate all needed files for use with AutoRun

      @{B}Templates@{UB}      - Templates for easy filling the @{B}Action@{UB} line
                      In the directory @{FG SHINE}Templates@{FG TEXT} you can find the
                      example.


@endnode

